Tutorial 7 – Smart Home Motor Control
Overview

This tutorial extends the smart home system by adding relay-based DC motor control, hardware interrupts, LCD feedback, keypad input, and serial monitoring on the STM32 Nucleo-F439ZI.

The system simulates a smart gate/door:

A = Open
B = Close
C = Stop
D = Change mode
Hardware
STM32 Nucleo-F439ZI
2-channel relay module
DC motor
20x4 I2C LCD
4x4 keypad
PIR sensor
Interrupt buttons / limit switches
Green and red indicator LEDs
330 Ω resistors for LEDs
Capacitors for motor noise suppression
Main pins
Relay IN1 → PF_2
Relay IN2 → PE_3
LCD SDA → PB_9 / D14
LCD SCL → PB_8 / D15
Keypad rows → PB_3, PB_5, PC_7, PA_15
Keypad cols → PB_12, PB_13, PB_15, PC_6
Features
Motor open / close / stop control
Interrupt-driven response
LCD motor status display
Keypad manual control
Serial monitor logging
LED direction indication
Example serial output
Motor=STOPPED | Mode=MANUAL | LastEvent=NONE | Alarm=OFF
Motor=CLOSING | Mode=MANUAL | LastEvent=KEY CLOSE | Alarm=OFF
Motor=OPENING | Mode=MANUAL | LastEvent=KEY OPEN | Alarm=OFF
Result

The final system successfully controlled the motor in both directions, stopped correctly, updated the LCD live, and responded to keypad and interrupt events in real time.
